<h1>Using Form Widgets</h1>

<p>All form widgets have a number of common behaviors.</p>

<h2>Flow</h2>

<h4>Block</h4>

<p>By default all form widgets use block positioning, and will flow each one below the other:</p>

<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div class="form-horizontal">
        <f-textbox placeholder="input 1"></f-textbox>
        <f-textbox placeholder="input 2"></f-textbox>
    </div>
</div>

<h4>Inline</h4>

<p>Use the <code>inline</code> attribute to make inputs display inline for compact forms:</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div class="form-horizontal">
        <f-textbox inline placeholder="input 1"></f-textbox>
        <f-textbox inline placeholder="input 2"></f-textbox>
    </div>
</div>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
{% set formWidgetExample1 %}
<f-textbox inline placeholder="input 1"></f-textbox>
<f-textbox inline placeholder="input 2"></f-textbox>{% endset %}{{formWidgetExample1|e}}
</pre>

<h2>Labels</h2>

<p>Add a label to any form widget</p>

<h4>Using attributes</h4>
<p>Simple and clean</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div class="form-horizontal">
        <f-textbox label="name"></f-textbox>
    </div>
</div>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
{% set formWidgetExample2 %}
<f-textbox label="name"></f-textbox>{% endset %}{{formWidgetExample2|e}}
</pre>

<h4>Set using tags</h4>
<p>Allows greater control over style.</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div class="form-horizontal">
        <f-textbox placeholder="name">
            <label><em>name</em></label>
        </f-textbox>
    </div>
</div>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
{% set formWidgetExample3 %}
<f-textbox placeholder="name">
    <label><em>name</em></label>
</f-textbox>{% endset %}{{formWidgetExample3|e}}
</pre>

