<h4>Message position</h4>

<p>There are three possible values for <code>message-position</code>:</p>

<ul>
    <li><b>auto:</b> if the message is one line, display inline. If it is multiline, display block</li>
    <li><b>inline:</b> always display message inline. If the message is more than one line, only the first will be shown.</li>
    <li><b>block:</b> always display message as block, even when there is only one line.</li>
</ul>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div class="form-horizontal">
        <f-textbox label="name" message-position="block" help-messages="Please enter your full name"></f-textbox>
    </div>
</div>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
{% set formWidgetExample7 %}
<f-textbox label="name" message-position="block" help-messages="Please enter your full name"></f-textbox>{% endset %}{{formWidgetExample7|e}}
</pre>

<h2>Required star</h2>
<p>A required star will automatically be added to required form inputs. However, if you want to force a required star to show, use the <code>required-star</code> attribute.</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example">
    <div class="form-horizontal">
        <f-textbox label="name" required-star></f-textbox>
    </div>
</div>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
{% set formWidgetExample8 %}
<f-textbox label="name" required-star></f-textbox>{% endset %}{{formWidgetExample8|e}}
</pre>

